Dia. 01 Black's Failure
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par In actual game there is big chance that Black plays at 1. However this move doesn't reduce White's liberties.
\par
\par White doesn't answer against this move, just takes away Black's liberty with 2. So Black has only two liberties left while White still has three liberties, which means \cf1\b Black lost the capturing race\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par }
